In a world where human modification becomes increasingly commonplace, the intersection of function and fashion becomes all the more important, as well.
Prioritizing functionality above all, this lightweight garment is equipped with a buckle for carrying additional items—a popular choice among those with more itinerant lifestyles.
A prominent fashion designer's first foray into creating combat attire. Aside from being fashionably relevant, the torso is also equipped with ultra-thin alloy armor plating.

Geared towards mobility-minded adventurers, this outfit completely abandons any protective design considerations.
A cold-resistant combat suit with powerful heat preservation functionality. Can resist low temperatures in severely cold regions.
The first combat suit with a split upper and lower design, breaking the shackles of tradition. However, the exposed torso has proved to be a polarizing aspect among critics.
The Hykros suit made of a material that maintains a constant temperature. Can keep you warm while protecting you from the sun. A sensible choice for travelers.
